# Required GitHub Secrets:
# - FTP_SERVER: Your FTP server hostname
# - FTP_USERNAME: Your FTP username
# - FTP_PASSWORD: Your FTP password
# - FTP_SERVER_DIR: Target directory on server (optional)
# - FTP_PROTOCOL: ftp or sftp (optional, defaults to ftp)
# - FTP_PORT: Port number (optional, defaults to 21)

# Security Notes:
# 1. Never commit actual credentials to the repository
# 2. Use GitHub Secrets for all sensitive information
# 3. Consider using SFTP instead of FTP for better security
# 4. Ensure your server has proper SSL certificates
# 5. Regular backup your database and files

